        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 5 at 3:50AM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 350 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 3
miles east of Red Shirt, or 34 miles southeast of Rapid City, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Red Shirt and western Badlands National Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
